uang Dictionary of Buddhism</title><biblScope unit="page">6428b</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-8d17a8f3-d898-45e5-a63a-896350e61c19">JINGDECHUANDENGLU</ref><title>景德傳燈錄 Jǐngdé chuándēng lù The Record of the Transmission of the Lamp Published in the Jǐngdé Era Taishō</title><biblScope unit="page">fasc. 1</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl></listBibl></form><sense xml:id="uuid-682194bc-7880-43c9-a0d6-15f3ff1f43ed"><gramGrp><pos>N</pos><tls:syn-func corresp="#uuid-c43c0bab-2810-42a4-a6be-e4641d9b6632">NPpr</tls:syn-func><tls:sem-feat corresp="#uuid-2e7204ae-4771-435b-82ff-310068296b6d">buddhist</tls:sem-feat></gramGrp><def>BUDDH: the Sixth Indian Patriarch according to the Chan/Zen tradition; skr. Bibhaka</def></sense></entry><entry type="word" xml:id="uuid-f0fae593-75dd-46b5-b358-ac94431281bd"><form corresp="#uuid-f7792e89-6029-42e2-999d-b6f8cf133e7c #uuid-a07df213-b938-43db-9782-7161ec468c87 #uuid-a9fcb847-0d11-4a78-b100-e0b1d53657a0"><orth>提多迦</orth><pron xml:lang="zh-Latn-x-pinyin">tí duō jiē</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-oc">ɡ-lee k-laal kal</pron><pron xml:lang="zh-x-mc">dei tɑ kʷɑ</pron><listBibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-7ab3ef94-ae67-4fe6-8275-5bd35fe84391">AYUWANGZHUAN(A)</ref><title>阿育王傳 Āyùwáng zhuàn Àxokarājāvadāna Taishō</title><biblScope unit="page">fasc.5</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-e89d8b37-8aa0-4bba-b117-3d688bbb15d6">AYUWANGZHUAN(B)</ref><title>阿育王傳 Āyùwáng zhuàn Àxokarājasūtra ? Taishō</title><biblScope unit="page">fasc.5</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-3ad389dc-bfb9-4140-8d56-35830939e3dc">BAOLINZHUAN</ref><title>寶林傳 Bǎolín zhuàn Transmissions from the Treasure Grove</title><biblScope unit="page">fasc. 2</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref target="#uuid-2389c812-8053-4187-8f7a-19f6e856050f">FOGUANG</ref><title>佛光大辭典 Fóguāng dàcídiǎn The Foguang Dictionary of Buddhism</title><biblScope unit="page">4957c-4958a</biblScope><note><p/></note></bibl><bibl><ref t